{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"445b06cd-94c8-422f-a54a-292fb6432a50","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (organizational) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Single-org Azure AD auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API style (default in .NET 6+)\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nFor JWT Bearer token auth without Azure AD, start with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"30f8906a-2255-407d-84e2-d8df43ac0770","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about creating a web API project with authentication - specifically what template to use and what authentication options are available. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context mentions dotnet plugins and NuGet packages).\n\nI can answer this from general knowledge without needing to search the codebase, as this is a standard .NET development question.","outputTokens":360,"requestId":"D003:A7C8:11D489B:141A0B3:69F93E85"},"id":"599ab74d-8ad6-46a1-93f2-787d0f48adec","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:49:18.353Z","parentId":"c56ef863-0792-43ef-b5f5-fd5a6be5fe64"}
